How to Connect Printer to Wifi Router | Convert Any Printer using Ethernet Port

My home printer Canon printer MF7500 series connected to router at IP: 192.168.1.2

go to 192.168.1.1 Router site
ADVANCED\Attached Devices
Canon Printer MF4700 IP: 192.168.1.2

Go to Windows 
Setting\Device\Printers & Scanners\Add a printer or scanner

Automatically Search printer under router 192.168.1.1
or input ip address 192.168.1.1 to search.
The Printer "Canon MF4700 Sedries" will be added list.

Download and install MF4700 driver MF4700MFDriversV2090W64usEN.exe (select networking driver) 
to my wifi connected hwang-laptop.

Click "Canon MF4700 Sedries" added list print will get driver with printer.
Canon MF4700 Series (FAX)
Canon MF4700 UFRII LT
Canon MF4700 UFRII LT XPS

After installed app 

"Canon MF4700 Sedries"\Manage\Properties 
Checked CNMFNP_2C9EFC62F5C8   Canon MFNP Port   Canon MF4700

Click Test Printer




